HEADWORD: Sphrigosis
<hw>Sphri*go"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/<?/<?/ to be full of strength.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
condition of vegetation in which there is too abundant growth of the
stem and leaves, accompanied by deficiency of flowers and
fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

